articles.title: No. 17 St. John's beats Marquette 76-70 to win 12th straight and take over Big East lead
articles.original_title: No. 17 St. John's beats Marquette 76-70 to win 12th straight and take over Big East lead
articles.summary: Bryce Hopkins had 23 points and 10 rebounds as No. 17 St. John's defeated Marquette 76-70 on Wednesday night to earn its 12th straight victory and move atop the Big East standings.  St. John's has won its last 11 Big East road games dating to last season.  Marquette freshman Nigel James Jr. made a three-point play that cut the St. John’s lead to 72-70 with 27.5 seconds left, but Zuby Ejiofor and Hopkins each made a pair of free throws to seal the victory.
